  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2021-07-06",
    "date": "2022-01-07T14:48:06Z",
    "text": "No Biometric Barriers to Housing Act of 2021\n\nThis bill prohibits owners of certain federally assisted rental units from using facial recognition, physical biometric recognition, or remote biometric recognition technology in any units or in any building or on any grounds containing such a unit.\n\nWithin one year, the Department of Housing and Urban Development must report on\u00a0any known use of such technology in federally assisted rental units in the preceding five years."
  },
